(43, 17, 14, 20, 29, 27, 27, 'the world hath hated them', 'Contrast Between Just and Unjust', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict between the just and the unjust. John 17:14 highlights the hatred faced by those not of the world, paralleling Proverbs 29:27''s depiction of the abomination felt by the just towards the unjust.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 14, 40, 10, 24, 25, 'the world hath hated them', 'Discipleship and Worldly Rejection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejection faced by Jesus'' followers. John 17:14 highlights that the world hates those who are not of it, while Matthew 10:24-25 illustrates that disciples will be treated as their master, facing similar hostility.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 14, 60, 4, 4, 5, 'the world hath hated them', 'Rejection by the World', 'This connection highlights the theme of being rejected by the world for not conforming to its ways. Both passages emphasize the idea that believers are distinct from the world and face hostility as a result.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
